This paper deals with a problem related to computational geometry, specifically the computation of the rectilinear convex hull of a set of points in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm used in the paper has a time complexity of O(nlogn) and space complexity of O(n), indicating that it involves some sort of data structure or algorithmic technique. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The problem of finding the rectilinear convex hull with minimum area can be seen as an optimization problem, which falls under the scope of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The concept of convex hulls is also relevant to cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and the problem of finding the minimum area hull can be seen as a control problem, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
